<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-584] convertToImage seems to invert colors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-584</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The pdfbox support team asked me to post this message on this forum so attachments could be seen&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a pdf document that has a white background with black text. It&lt;br/&gt;
appears after I make the call to convertToImage the colors are reversed. A&lt;br/&gt;
black background with white text&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pdDocument = PDDocument.load(new ByteArrayInputStream(aContent));&lt;br/&gt;
List&amp;lt;PDPage&amp;gt; documentPageList = pdDocument.getDocumentCatalog().getAllPages();&lt;br/&gt;
for(int i=0; i&amp;lt;documentPageList.size(); ++i) {&lt;br/&gt;
PDPage aPage = documentPageList.get&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
for (int x=1; x &amp;lt; 14; x++) {&lt;br/&gt;
BufferedImage tempImage = convertToImage(x, (2 * 72),aPage);&lt;br/&gt;
ImageIO.write(tempImage,&quot;jpeg&quot;, new File(&quot;c:&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;tmp&lt;br/&gt;
page-&quot; + x + &quot;.jpeg&quot;));&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;/p&gt;</description>
