                            <comment id="12791415" author="styriver" created="Wed, 16 Dec 2009 15:48:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Original is the pdf we are attempting to convert&lt;br/&gt;
The page-8.png file is the out from convertToImage call&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12791435" author="m.martinez" created="Wed, 16 Dec 2009 16:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen this same problem (reversed color tables) in numerous PDF files with JPEG and BMP images.  When I extract the images with the seqence:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PDPage page = ....&lt;br/&gt;
PDResources resources = page.getResources();&lt;br/&gt;
Map images = resources.getImages();&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
PDXObjectImage image = (PDXObjectImage)images.get(key);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;writing out the image from this object results in an image with the colors inverted, as if looking at a color negative.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Interestingly, they generally are correct for straight black &amp;amp; white images.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried various sequences for extracting the image from the PDXObjectImage object, but the result is always the same.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is with 0.8.0 incubator.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850679" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 28 Mar 2010 14:33:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With version 928408 the colors aren&apos;t inverted anymore, see attached image.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893134" author="gaurav.jain3@cognizant.com" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 10:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same problem exists. I&apos;m still getting image in which color is&lt;br/&gt;
different. Just like seeing a negative. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
